name: Kamran Ghulam
summary: In the second Test match between Pakistan and England in Multan, Pakistan's Kamran Ghulam made a significant impact on his debut. The 33-year-old batter scored a century, becoming the second-oldest player to do so on his Test debut for Pakistan. Despite a dropped catch by England's Ben Duckett, Ghulam's innings played a crucial role in Pakistan's recovery after losing early wickets. The century helped Pakistan reach a respectable 259 for five on day one, preventing England from gaining a significant advantage. Ghulam's performance has been praised by experts, highlighting his determination and the opportunity provided by the selectors.

name: North Korean South Korea
summary: North Korea has heightened tensions with South Korea by destroying roads connecting the two countries. This action follows a drone launch by the South, which prompted North Korea to threaten retaliation. The Guardian reports that North Korea has also threatened to "turn South Korea into piles of ashes." South Korea has responded by warning the North against further provocations. The Independent reports that North Korea has cut off all roads to the South, a move that has raised concerns about cross-border aggression. The Financial Times describes the road demolition as a "display of cross-border aggression." The situation remains tense, with both countries on high alert.

name: Neil Critchley
summary: Neil Critchley, the former Blackpool manager, has been appointed as the new head coach of Heart of Midlothian Football Club (Hearts FC). The news was announced on social media and other news outlets, with Critchley replacing Steven Naismith after a short tenure. Hearts had been in talks with Critchley for some time, with Per-Mathias Hogmo also being linked with the position. Steven Gerrard, the former Rangers manager, has expressed his support for Critchley, dismissing any comparisons to Michael Beale, his former assistant at Ibrox. With Critchley's appointment, Hearts aim to strengthen their position in the Scottish Premiership, where they currently sit in sixth place.

name: Mbappe
summary: Kylian Mbappe, the star player for Real Madrid, recently faced controversy and legal action. Reports of a rape allegation surfaced, leading to intense media coverage and public outrage. Mbappe strongly denied the accusations and criticized media outlets for spreading false information. In response to the allegations, authorities confirmed an ongoing investigation but did not specify whether Mbappe was involved. Amidst the turmoil, Mbappe expressed his frustration and demanded accountability from those responsible for spreading "fake news." Despite the allegations, Mbappe continued to train and fulfill his commitments with Real Madrid. His performance and statistics remain impressive, raising questions about his priorities and resilience in the face of adversity. The situation has sparked debates about the role of the media in reporting sensitive allegations, the pressure faced by public figures, and the impact on Mbappe's reputation and career.
